[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]PROPOSED REFORMS
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]They are certainly needed but I d
[normal]oubt whether they are sufficient to make all the improvements
[normal] that could be achieved given the right emphasis and direction
[normal]. They are a good stepping stone but are not the complete answer. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]These proposed reforms will only be effective to a limited extent. They will highlight the problem and identify the areas of failure and point out the providers and local authorities who are falling below acceptable minimum standards. What is 
[normal]missing is the cure to the problems of children being place in underperforming homes in remote locations.
